If I have a chalice application that contains a routed function and that in turn invokes another separate function any AWS actions in that second function are not picked up and added to the policy, for example with the following test applicaiton:
```
import boto3
import uuid
import time
from chalice import Chalice


NAME = "test"
app = Chalice(app_name=NAME)
DB_CLIENT = boto3.client('dynamodb')

@app.route('/new')
def put():
    tid = str(uuid.uuid4())
    item={
        'tid': {'S':tid},
        'text':{'S':'Test Data'}
    }
    DB_CLIENT.put_item(TableName=NAME, Item=item)
    return {'tid': tid}

@app.route('/find/{tid}')
def get(tid):
    text = get_text(tid)
    return {'text' : text}

def get_text(tid):
    r = DB_CLIENT.get_item(TableName=NAME, Key={'tid':{'S':tid}})
    data = r['Item']
    return data['text']['S']
```
This is the policy that is generated
```
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
